  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves the process of making illegally-gained proceeds appear legitimate by disguising their true origin. This practice undermines the integrity of financial systems and is often associated with organized crime, corruption, and terrorism financing.\n\nIn China, the fight against money laundering is taken seriously. The country has established a comprehensive legal framework to combat this crime, including the Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China. The Chinese government also cooperates with international counterparts to prevent and control money laundering activities, reflecting China's commitment to upholding the rule of law and contributing to the global effort to combat financial crimes.",
